WEBVTT

00:18.167 --> 00:20.968
( ominous music playing )

00:34.300 --> 00:36.801
Narrator:
<i>In September 2013,</i>

00:36.868 --> 00:38.234
<i>al-Shabaab,</i>

00:38.300 --> 00:41.033
<i>an al-Qaeda-linked
terrorist group from Somalia,</i>

00:41.100 --> 00:44.000
<i>attacked a shopping mall
in neighboring Kenya.</i>

00:52.901 --> 00:55.834
<i>More than 100 security cameras
recorded the attack,</i>

00:55.901 --> 00:58.868
<i>which left 71 people dead.</i>

01:01.567 --> 01:04.467
<i>Some footage was
destroyed by fire...</i>

01:04.534 --> 01:06.334
<i>but much of it survives</i>

01:06.400 --> 01:09.367
<i>and it documents the attack
in stark detail.</i>

01:11.067 --> 01:13.701
<i>But it also reveals
something else--</i>

01:13.767 --> 01:15.734
<i>the courage
and resilience</i>

01:15.801 --> 01:19.567
<i>by which so many
ordinary civilians survived</i>

01:19.634 --> 01:22.300
<i>mass murder
in a crowded shopping mall.</i>

01:34.267 --> 01:36.767
♪ ♪

01:44.234 --> 01:46.434
Jasmine Postwalla:
<i>Westgate was one place</i>
<i>where you meet</i>

01:46.500 --> 01:49.234
people of different cultures,
different tribes,

01:49.300 --> 01:51.934
different religions,
different everything.

01:52.000 --> 01:54.133
I mean, just-- I think that
was the most special thing.

01:54.200 --> 01:56.434
♪ ♪

01:59.334 --> 02:02.067
Narrator:
<i>At the front of the mall,</i>
<i>overlooking the street</i>

02:02.133 --> 02:03.868
<i>were three
busy restaurants:</i>

02:03.934 --> 02:05.934
<i>Urban Burger,</i>

02:06.000 --> 02:07.601
<i>Tapas,</i>

02:07.667 --> 02:09.601
<i>and Artcaffe.</i>

02:11.000 --> 02:13.400
Frank:
<i>It was the best mall</i>
<i>in Nairobi.</i>

02:13.467 --> 02:15.567
<i>It was very up-market.</i>

02:15.634 --> 02:17.767
It's the place where
prominent people come.

02:17.834 --> 02:19.968
♪ ♪

02:20.033 --> 02:22.334
Narrator:
<i>At the back of the mall</i>
<i>was Nakumatt,</i>

02:22.400 --> 02:26.133
<i>a giant supermarket
on two floors.</i>

02:26.200 --> 02:30.567
Amber Prior:
<i>Nakumatt at Westgate was the</i>
<i>premier supermarket in Nairobi.</i>

02:30.634 --> 02:31.901
<i>It had an escalator.</i>

02:31.968 --> 02:33.868
<i>That was a huge thing
for Kenya, you know,</i>

02:33.934 --> 02:36.801
<i>to have an escalator
inside a supermarket.</i>

02:36.868 --> 02:38.500
It sold everything
that you might need

02:38.567 --> 02:40.634
and that was
always their tag line:
"All under one roof."

02:42.601 --> 02:44.901
Katherine Walton:
<i>We'd be there two,</i>
<i>three times during the week.</i>

02:44.968 --> 02:48.767
You know, it was more
than just a mall to buy,
you know, extra stuff.

02:48.834 --> 02:50.033
It was really
a part of our lives.

02:50.100 --> 02:52.334
♪ ♪

02:56.968 --> 02:58.701
Amber:
<i>That Saturday was really</i>

02:58.767 --> 03:00.868
<i>a normal Saturday
like any other Saturday.</i>

03:00.934 --> 03:03.400
<i>I went with my kids--</i>

03:03.467 --> 03:06.167
<i>my daughter Amelie
who's six years old,</i>

03:06.234 --> 03:08.801
<i>and my son Elliott
who's four.</i>

03:08.868 --> 03:10.667
I was quite excited
to do my shop,

03:10.734 --> 03:12.701
because I was doing
a big shop and I don't go
to Nakumatt very often.

03:12.767 --> 03:14.868
I try to do all my shopping
at the local supermarket,

03:14.934 --> 03:17.067
but I was finding stuff you
don't normally find, you know.

03:17.133 --> 03:19.534
I'm French and I remember
finding Orangina,

03:19.601 --> 03:22.367
which is a drink you get in
France and I remember thinking--
getting really excited about it.

03:26.100 --> 03:28.701
Margie:
<i>We were planning on getting</i>
<i>as many groceries as we could.</i>

03:28.767 --> 03:30.734
<i>We needed to do it
relatively quickly,</i>

03:30.801 --> 03:32.300
<i>because I had a little baby</i>

03:32.367 --> 03:35.434
who was eight months old,
and he was heading
close to naptime.

03:35.500 --> 03:38.534
So it was kinda that shop
where we took our time,

03:38.601 --> 03:41.434
but we were thinking, "Okay,
baby's gonna lose it soon.
He needs to get home."

03:41.500 --> 03:44.067
♪ ♪

03:44.133 --> 03:46.167
Narrator:
<i>Opposite Nakumatt's entrance</i>

03:46.234 --> 03:49.133
<i>Valentine Kadzo had
set up a display table</i>

03:49.200 --> 03:50.801
<i>for a computer company.</i>

03:50.868 --> 03:54.534
Valentine:
<i>I was at Westgate</i>
<i>because I was working.</i>

03:54.601 --> 03:56.868
<i>We had a display table.</i>

03:56.934 --> 03:58.968
We have the products,

03:59.033 --> 04:01.234
so that the customer
can touch and feel.

04:01.300 --> 04:03.067
♪ ♪

04:03.133 --> 04:05.534
Narrator:
<i>A few feet from Valentine's</i>
<i>display table</i>

04:05.601 --> 04:08.000
<i>Katherine Walton stopped
to make a phone call.</i>

04:08.067 --> 04:10.901
Katherine:
<i>The kids just wanted</i>
<i>to hang out a bit</i>

04:10.968 --> 04:12.500
<i>and have some lunch.</i>

04:12.567 --> 04:13.734
I have two boys--

04:13.801 --> 04:15.868
a 14-year-old
and a 10-year-old--

04:15.934 --> 04:17.467
and then three little girls--

04:17.534 --> 04:19.801
four, two
and then 13 months.

04:19.868 --> 04:22.901
Narrator:
<i>Katherine's two sons</i>
<i>had gone shopping</i>

04:22.968 --> 04:25.000
<i>in the supermarket.</i>

04:25.067 --> 04:27.234
Blaise:
<i>We stopped</i>
<i>at the drink aisle</i>

04:27.300 --> 04:29.300
'cause I wanted
something to drink.

04:29.367 --> 04:31.033
So I tried calling my mom
for a few minutes,

04:31.100 --> 04:33.167
then I gave up,
and then we went
and stood in line.

04:33.234 --> 04:35.467
♪ ♪

04:38.133 --> 04:40.033
Amber:
<i>We were there</i>
<i>for quite a while.</i>

04:40.100 --> 04:42.634
<i>I think we'd probably
already been in Nakumatt
for about an hour or so.</i>

04:42.701 --> 04:45.934
<i>Our trolley was full.
We were almost finished.</i>

04:46.000 --> 04:48.300
And then I remembered I wanted
to get a bottle of wine,

04:48.367 --> 04:50.601
so I actually left the kids
by the shopping trolley,

04:50.667 --> 04:52.434
<i>which in Kenya
you kind of do,</i>

04:52.500 --> 04:55.701
<i>'cause you don't have that
culture of fear of your kids
getting kidnapped</i>

04:55.767 --> 04:59.567
<i>or the things like that,
so you know that they're
quite safe.</i>

04:59.634 --> 05:01.701
Narrator:
<i>At 12:30 Andrew Munyua</i>

05:01.767 --> 05:04.834
<i>was at the street entrance
to the mall.</i>

05:04.901 --> 05:07.000
I thought of just
passing through Westgate,

05:07.067 --> 05:10.334
do a few errands,
buy some packed lunch

05:10.400 --> 05:13.868
and then later on pick my boy
and come back home, like normal.

05:13.934 --> 05:16.000
You have to go
through security check

05:16.067 --> 05:18.968
and I was at the door,
when I was being searched

05:19.033 --> 05:20.934
and my hands was raised up.

05:21.000 --> 05:24.500
Katherine:
<i>I was just walking</i>
<i>in front of Nakumatt</i>

05:24.567 --> 05:26.534
<i>when there was
a loud explosion.</i>

05:26.601 --> 05:28.133
Andrew:<i> Bang!</i>
( dramatic music playing )

05:28.200 --> 05:29.968
<i>I realized the guard that</i>

05:30.033 --> 05:32.901
was searching me
had now fallen down.

05:34.133 --> 05:35.100
Jon Quail:
<i>The grenade went off,</i>

05:35.167 --> 05:38.868
<i>immediately followed
by gunfire.</i>

05:38.934 --> 05:41.801
<i>You could see people
falling on the floor.</i>

05:41.868 --> 05:43.400
Some were diving
for cover,

05:43.467 --> 05:44.868
but some were
actually falling.

05:46.601 --> 05:48.467
Andrew:
<i>When I dived down,</i>

05:48.534 --> 05:50.467
<i>I decided to touch
my chest.</i>

05:50.534 --> 05:53.634
I checked down
and I saw there was
blood on my fingers.

05:55.300 --> 05:57.067
Narrator:
<i>Niall Saville</i>
<i>and his wife Moon Hee</i>

05:57.133 --> 06:00.033
<i>had been having lunch
on the terrace at Urban Burger.</i>

06:00.100 --> 06:03.868
Niall:
<i>I realized that my wife</i>
<i>wasn't actually behind me.</i>

06:03.934 --> 06:06.467
I saw her crawling
on the ground,

06:06.534 --> 06:09.033
clearly in a lot of pain.

06:09.100 --> 06:11.734
Her legs looked
very bloodied.

06:13.534 --> 06:15.701
<i>I took her arm
and dragged her</i>

06:15.767 --> 06:18.701
<i>towards the back wall
of the burger restaurant,</i>

06:18.767 --> 06:21.534
<i>so that we didn't have
a direct line onto the road,</i>

06:21.601 --> 06:24.434
assuming that it was
a hit-and-run grenade attack,

06:24.500 --> 06:26.534
and therefore
being out of sight of the road

06:26.601 --> 06:28.234
was the important thing
at that point.

06:28.300 --> 06:31.033
♪ ♪

06:31.100 --> 06:33.701
Katherine:
<i>Tracer rounds.</i>
<i>They were tracer rounds.</i>

06:33.767 --> 06:37.200
You know, there was that
flash of light as they were
flying through the air.

06:39.767 --> 06:42.234
Valentine:
<i>People were confused,</i>
<i>they don't know where to go--</i>

06:42.300 --> 06:45.367
stepping on each other.
That's when I saw a white lady

06:45.434 --> 06:47.367
with three children.

06:47.434 --> 06:51.500
<i>So they were running
in different directions.
That's when I picked one.</i>

06:51.567 --> 06:54.434
Katherine:
<i>You know, I started to run</i>
<i>and then a Kenyan woman came</i>

06:54.500 --> 06:56.300
<i>and grabbed one
of the girls from me.</i>

06:56.367 --> 06:58.200
<i>And we dove behind this</i>

06:58.267 --> 07:01.667
<i>computer display table
that was there.</i>

07:01.734 --> 07:03.500
She had Portia,
my four-year-old,

07:03.567 --> 07:05.434
and was laying on top
of her to protect her.

07:06.868 --> 07:08.901
Narrator:
<i>Now Diljeet Kaur and a friend</i>

07:08.968 --> 07:12.167
<i>also squeezed in
under the display table.</i>

07:12.234 --> 07:14.968
My friend was
lying like that

07:15.033 --> 07:17.467
and that Kenyan lady
was lying like that.

07:17.534 --> 07:20.467
Katherine:
<i>It was a tight fit</i>
<i>with the seven of us.</i>

07:20.534 --> 07:23.901
We were kind of laying on top
of each other and all
scrunched up.

07:25.801 --> 07:27.367
Narrator:
<i>As the gunfire got closer</i>

07:27.434 --> 07:31.667
<i>people surged
from the main mall
into the supermarket.</i>

07:33.033 --> 07:35.400
As we were running,
people just came

07:35.467 --> 07:37.567
and started pushing me
and Blaise and, like,

07:37.634 --> 07:39.868
<i>I had to reach
my arm through just
to grab his hand</i>

07:39.934 --> 07:42.100
<i>so I wouldn't be
separated from him.</i>

07:44.100 --> 07:46.634
Amber:
<i>People were running</i>
<i>towards the back of Nakumatt</i>

07:46.701 --> 07:49.868
<i>and that's when I thought,
"I've got to get to the kids."</i>

07:49.934 --> 07:53.000
Because it was quite chaotic,
I couldn't remember
exactly which till,

07:53.067 --> 07:54.234
so it took me a while
to sort of find them.

07:54.300 --> 07:56.167
And I remember screaming,
"Amelie, Amelie,"

07:56.234 --> 07:58.234
<i>to try and pinpoint
where they were.</i>

07:58.300 --> 08:01.434
♪ ♪

08:01.500 --> 08:03.400
( gunfire )

08:06.133 --> 08:08.834
Narrator:
<i>Inside Nakumatt,</i>
<i>a customer's cell phone</i>

08:08.901 --> 08:11.601
<i>recorded the gunfire
getting closer...</i>

08:11.667 --> 08:13.100
Woman: What's happening?
( gunfire )

08:13.167 --> 08:15.133
Narrator:
<i>The two gunmen were</i>
<i>moving from the street...</i>

08:15.200 --> 08:17.000
( gunfire )

08:17.067 --> 08:19.267
<i>...to the restaurants
by the front entrance
of the mall.</i>

08:19.334 --> 08:22.601
♪ ♪

08:25.067 --> 08:27.467
Niall:
<i>I was looking at his face.</i>

08:27.534 --> 08:29.200
<i>He was young.</i>

08:29.267 --> 08:31.601
And he looked at me
and he fired.

08:41.400 --> 08:45.334
<i>As I pulled my wife behind
one of the counters</i>

08:45.400 --> 08:48.100
<i>and as I kind of collapsed
on the floor,</i>

08:48.167 --> 08:50.500
I realized
that I'd been shot.

08:51.801 --> 08:54.067
Narrator:
<i>100 feet away,</i>
<i>at Dormans Café,</i>

08:54.133 --> 08:55.667
<i>Nuriana Merali
and her little brother</i>

08:55.734 --> 08:57.467
<i>had been waiting
for their mother.</i>

08:57.534 --> 09:02.033
<i>With them was a school friend,
15-year-old Makena Kinyua.</i>

09:02.100 --> 09:04.434
Makena:
<i>'Cause we were trying</i>
<i>to stay as low as we could,</i>

09:04.500 --> 09:07.000
'cause we knew that
the people were shooting
from the main entrance.

09:08.234 --> 09:10.100
<i>I could see people
running into Nakumatt,</i>

09:10.167 --> 09:12.601
<i>so we ran inside Nakumatt.</i>

09:13.901 --> 09:16.000
Narrator:
<i>There was a lull</i>
<i>as the gunmen</i>

09:16.067 --> 09:17.567
<i>reloaded their weapons.</i>

09:18.534 --> 09:19.834
<i>Waiter Mike Kagwe</i>

09:19.901 --> 09:22.968
<i>saw Andrew wounded
and went to help him.</i>

09:23.033 --> 09:25.500
I think at that moment
somebody came and pulled me

09:25.567 --> 09:27.667
from the Dormans.
I had to tell him,

09:27.734 --> 09:29.834
( speaks Swahili )

09:29.901 --> 09:32.868
<i>"Stand up. Let's run."</i>

09:32.934 --> 09:35.701
Narrator:
<i>Mike rushed Andrew</i>
<i>into Nakumatt</i>

09:35.767 --> 09:36.934
<i>towards the loading bays,</i>

09:37.000 --> 09:39.267
<i>where hundreds of shoppers
were trying to escape.</i>

09:39.334 --> 09:41.634
♪ ♪

09:44.033 --> 09:46.300
<i>The gunmen now moved
from the restaurants</i>

09:46.367 --> 09:49.067
<i>towards Nakumatt.</i>

09:51.868 --> 09:54.267
Katherine:
<i>We were all laying</i>
<i>as flat as we could</i>

09:54.334 --> 09:56.534
<i>behind that table.</i>

09:56.601 --> 09:59.601
In the beginning I cried.
I was just so scared.

09:59.667 --> 10:01.400
And the Kenyan lady,
you know,

10:01.467 --> 10:03.434
kinda tapped me
on the shoulder and said,

10:03.500 --> 10:06.300
"You can't do that.
You have to be strong
for your girls."

10:07.934 --> 10:10.801
Valentine:
<i>The white lady told</i>
<i>the little girl I was holding,</i>

10:10.868 --> 10:13.200
"Put your fingers
in your ear

10:13.267 --> 10:16.467
and lay down
and keep quiet."

10:16.534 --> 10:19.033
♪ ♪

10:19.100 --> 10:21.467
Narrator:
<i>Two policemen guarding</i>
<i>a bank on the first floor</i>

10:21.534 --> 10:23.467
<i>spotted the terrorists
and opened fire.</i>

10:25.334 --> 10:27.634
Ali Miraji:
<i>I was using my rounds</i>
<i>to cover myself,</i>

10:27.701 --> 10:32.234
<i>shooting so rapidly
so that I could deny him
a chance to shoot at me.</i>

10:33.334 --> 10:35.100
I shot
him at his
right leg,

10:35.167 --> 10:37.500
almost around
his knee there.

10:37.567 --> 10:42.133
<i>He was limping, so I knew
that the guy was injured.</i>

10:42.200 --> 10:46.367
Narrator:
<i>Undeterred, the terrorists</i>
<i>headed on towards Nakumatt</i>

10:46.434 --> 10:48.234
<i>and the display table
where the four women</i>

10:48.300 --> 10:49.667
<i>and three children
were hiding.</i>

10:49.734 --> 10:51.334
♪ ♪

10:51.400 --> 10:53.334
Katherine:
<i>Petra kept crying.</i>

10:53.400 --> 10:56.100
<i>She would really scream
when the shooting would start.</i>

10:56.167 --> 10:58.868
<i>She would just scream
and scream.</i>

10:58.934 --> 11:01.567
I had brought one bottle
of milk with me

11:01.634 --> 11:03.400
and I gave that to her

11:03.467 --> 11:05.834
and she drank it
and went to sleep.

11:11.267 --> 11:13.133
<i>I realized that</i>

11:13.200 --> 11:15.634
<i>I would definitely--
as being an American,</i>

11:15.701 --> 11:17.500
<i>as being a Christian,</i>

11:17.567 --> 11:22.667
<i>that it was much more dangerous
probably for me.</i>

11:23.834 --> 11:25.601
You know,
I was a prime target.

11:25.667 --> 11:28.067
♪ ♪

11:28.133 --> 11:31.400
Narrator:
<i>As the first two gunmen</i>
<i>entered Nakumatt...</i>

11:32.834 --> 11:35.500
<i>two more were making
for the mall's upper entrance.</i>

11:38.200 --> 11:41.033
Woman on radio:
<i>That's right, it's all</i>
<i>happening today</i>

11:41.100 --> 11:44.000
<i>at the rooftop of Westgate.
We've got...</i>

11:44.067 --> 11:46.033
Narrator:
<i>They headed towards the rooftop</i>

11:46.100 --> 11:48.734
<i>where a children's
cooking competition
was taking place.</i>

11:48.801 --> 11:50.300
Woman on radio:
<i>What are you making today?</i>

11:50.367 --> 11:52.367
Girl:
<i>We're making apple pudding</i>

11:52.434 --> 11:54.067
<i>and-- with cream cheese delight</i>

11:54.133 --> 11:57.100
<i>and we're making
a crunchy tofu salad.</i>

11:57.167 --> 12:00.133
Jasmine:
<i>We heard gunshots,</i>
<i>we heard screaming.</i>

12:00.200 --> 12:02.267
I personally
felt that
this is

12:02.334 --> 12:03.400
a robbery
or something

12:03.467 --> 12:04.834
and these
are thugs.

12:04.901 --> 12:06.968
They need a passage,
so you stay out of the way

12:07.033 --> 12:08.334
and everything
will be okay.

12:08.400 --> 12:10.100
♪ ♪

12:10.167 --> 12:13.500
Simon Belcher:
<i>It was almost like we were</i>
<i>being herded like sheep.</i>

12:13.567 --> 12:16.167
<i>So we went to the furthest
corner of the parking lot</i>

12:16.234 --> 12:18.834
on the roof, away from
the door and the ramp.

12:18.901 --> 12:21.367
And there were a lot of people
stuck in there, lots of--

12:21.434 --> 12:24.000
lots of women
and children from the...

12:24.067 --> 12:25.968
Cooking competition, yeah.
cooking competition.

12:26.033 --> 12:28.834
♪ ♪

12:28.901 --> 12:31.667
Then suddenly we just saw people
falling one after the other.

12:31.734 --> 12:33.067
♪ ♪

12:33.133 --> 12:35.667
Amanda:
<i>As they shot,</i>
<i>you could hear the sound</i>

12:35.734 --> 12:38.033
<i>of the bullet
thud into someone.</i>

12:38.100 --> 12:40.701
The sound of the bullet
going into flesh

12:40.767 --> 12:42.934
is like nothing
you've ever heard.

12:43.000 --> 12:45.834
Doof! It feels like
somebody's being thumped.

12:45.901 --> 12:49.200
You know?
And then they just drop.

12:49.267 --> 12:52.300
I looked at them
when his gun was
pointing at me

12:52.367 --> 12:54.033
and he shot me
in the thigh.

12:54.100 --> 12:57.000
<i>And then I realized that I was
shot in the stomach as well.</i>

12:57.067 --> 12:58.968
♪ ♪

12:59.033 --> 13:01.000
I just put up
my hand and I said,
"Please let the children go.

13:01.067 --> 13:02.400
Just let the children go."

13:02.467 --> 13:05.634
The only thing he said was
that, "We're here to kill.

13:05.701 --> 13:08.300
You killed our people
in Somalia.

13:08.367 --> 13:11.400
We normally don't kill
women and children,

13:11.467 --> 13:15.601
but you killed ours in Somalia,
so we're here to take revenge."

13:15.667 --> 13:19.000
♪ ♪

13:19.067 --> 13:22.300
Aleem:
<i>I started saying</i>
<i>the Shahada really loudly.</i>

13:22.367 --> 13:25.033
( speaks Arabic )

13:25.100 --> 13:26.901
Which is...

13:26.968 --> 13:28.934
"There's no God but Allah,

13:29.000 --> 13:30.467
and Muhammad is
his messenger."

13:30.534 --> 13:31.834
♪ ♪

13:31.901 --> 13:34.067
<i>So as soon as he heard that,
the gunman looked at me</i>

13:34.133 --> 13:37.100
<i>and he said,
"Are you Muslim?"
And I said, "Yes, I am."</i>

13:37.167 --> 13:39.801
<i>By that time my wife
had come next to me.</i>

13:39.868 --> 13:42.434
She was drenched
in blood

13:42.500 --> 13:44.167
from top to toe.

13:44.234 --> 13:46.500
<i>He said,
"Is this your woman?"</i>

13:46.567 --> 13:48.434
<i>And I said,
"Yes, she is."</i>

13:48.500 --> 13:50.467
And then he said, "Go."

13:52.100 --> 13:55.300
Narrator:
<i>As Aleem and his wife</i>
<i>ran down the ramp to safety,</i>

13:55.367 --> 13:57.801
<i>the gunmen released
some other Muslims</i>

13:57.868 --> 14:00.167
<i>who'd also survived
the initial attack.</i>

14:01.467 --> 14:03.100
Anne Muigai:
<i>An elderly lady stood up,</i>

14:03.167 --> 14:07.000
<i>encouraged to see
that the gunman was
releasing people.</i>

14:07.067 --> 14:08.400
So she said,
"Oh, I'm old.

14:08.467 --> 14:09.834
I can't kneel
any more.

14:09.901 --> 14:12.100
My knees
are arthritic.

14:12.167 --> 14:15.567
I'm in a lot of pain.
Please let me go."

14:15.634 --> 14:18.801
And then the man asked her,
"Are you a Muslim?"

14:18.868 --> 14:21.968
And while
the woman was thinking
of the answer to give,

14:22.033 --> 14:24.667
the gunman just shot her.

14:26.334 --> 14:28.734
Narrator:
<i>The gunfire on the rooftop</i>
<i>caused panic</i>

14:28.801 --> 14:30.167
<i>amongst shoppers
trying to escape</i>

14:30.234 --> 14:32.334
<i>through the loading bays
down below.</i>

14:32.400 --> 14:34.868
Amber:
<i>Lots of people came running</i>
<i>out of the storeroom,</i>

14:34.934 --> 14:36.167
<i>back into
Nakumatt supermarket,</i>

14:36.234 --> 14:37.701
<i>screaming,
"Don't go that way!</i>

14:37.767 --> 14:39.033
<i>They're shooting that way."</i>

14:39.100 --> 14:40.400
So then we were
really stuck.

14:40.467 --> 14:41.667
We couldn't get out the front

14:41.734 --> 14:43.000
and we thought
we couldn't get out the back.

14:43.067 --> 14:45.434
♪ ♪

14:48.033 --> 14:50.634
Narrator:
<i>The gunmen in Nakumatt</i>
<i>made an announcement</i>

14:50.701 --> 14:53.667
<i>on the supermarket's
public address system.</i>

14:53.734 --> 14:55.400
"This al-Shabaab
attack

14:55.467 --> 14:57.434
and we're going
to kill everybody!

14:57.500 --> 14:58.534
You came
to our land.

14:58.601 --> 15:00.601
You killed
our women and children.

15:00.667 --> 15:02.634
"It's our time."

15:04.267 --> 15:06.267
Margie:
<i>Where do you hide</i>
<i>in a supermarket?</i>

15:06.334 --> 15:08.167
<i>Anywhere you are,
you're exposed.</i>

15:08.234 --> 15:10.534
And I kept on thinking,
"Why now?

15:10.601 --> 15:11.968
I can't believe
this is happening

15:12.033 --> 15:13.167
while I have
my baby with me."

15:13.234 --> 15:16.400
♪ ♪

15:16.467 --> 15:18.300
Amber:
<i>I thought the best place</i>
<i>to hide would be</i>

15:18.367 --> 15:21.133
behind the meat section,
behind the deli counters,
if you like.

15:21.200 --> 15:25.400
Narrator:
<i>Nuriana and Makena also hid</i>
<i>behind the meat counter.</i>

15:25.467 --> 15:28.033
Makena:
<i>Nuriana's mom was lying</i>
<i>in front of me,</i>

15:28.100 --> 15:30.400
then next to her
was Nuriana

15:30.467 --> 15:34.434
and then behind Nuriana
was her younger brother.

15:34.500 --> 15:36.834
Everybody was just
lying down, face down...

15:36.901 --> 15:39.767
and trying to move
as little as possible.

15:39.834 --> 15:42.100
I said, "Can I come
and hide back here?"

15:42.167 --> 15:43.534
And they said,
"Sure, just--"

15:43.601 --> 15:45.067
and they showed me
where to come in,

15:45.133 --> 15:46.467
so I kinda ducked down.

15:46.534 --> 15:48.500
I'm still holding
my 8-month-old baby.

15:48.567 --> 15:50.567
( ominous music playing )

15:50.634 --> 15:53.200
Narrator:
<i>The security camera footage</i>
<i>from the meat counter</i>

15:53.267 --> 15:54.534
<i>was never recovered.</i>

15:54.601 --> 15:57.834
<i>But cameras nearby
show the areas</i>

15:57.901 --> 16:00.434
<i>to the left
and to the right.</i>

16:00.500 --> 16:02.033
Amber:
<i>The occasional phone</i>
<i>would ring,</i>

16:02.100 --> 16:03.133
<i>"and everybody
would be like, "Shhh!</i>

16:03.200 --> 16:05.067
<i>Turn it off!
Put it on silent!"</i>

16:05.133 --> 16:07.234
Sometimes,
I would look up...

16:07.300 --> 16:09.968
and the other mothers
would look at me,

16:10.033 --> 16:12.167
and we would
sort of nod to each other--
kind of encouraging nods

16:12.234 --> 16:13.634
to say, "Look,
it's gonna be okay."

16:16.968 --> 16:18.901
Narrator:
<i>Bleeding from a shrapnel wound,</i>

16:18.968 --> 16:20.767
<i>Andrew had taken refuge</i>

16:20.834 --> 16:23.167
<i>in Nakumatt's
furniture storeroom.</i>

16:23.234 --> 16:25.467
Andrew:
<i>I'm starting to feel dizzy.</i>

16:25.534 --> 16:27.934
I'm starting
to feel nervous.

16:28.000 --> 16:29.500
I'm now starting
to think

16:29.567 --> 16:32.000
how this could be the end
of ourselves, you know?

16:32.067 --> 16:34.067
<i>I don't know whether
we'll be out of the mall.</i>

16:34.133 --> 16:36.300
<i>I'm bleeding,
and I'm starting to fear now.</i>

16:36.367 --> 16:39.267
I was thinking like,
"Oh, this is the end
of the story now."

16:39.334 --> 16:41.133
♪ ♪

16:41.200 --> 16:43.167
<i>They ushered me
into a room</i>

16:43.234 --> 16:45.934
<i>where they administered
first aid.</i>

16:46.000 --> 16:48.200
That's when he told me
that he's thirsty.

16:48.267 --> 16:51.200
He wants water
and to me--

16:51.267 --> 16:53.734
I told him that,
"Just stay put.
Wait for me.

16:53.801 --> 16:55.367
Let me go look for water.
I bring it to you."

16:55.434 --> 16:57.567
♪ ♪

16:57.634 --> 16:58.901
Narrator:
<i>As Mike went</i>
<i>downstairs</i>

16:58.968 --> 17:00.467
<i>to fetch water
for Andrew...</i>

17:01.334 --> 17:03.033
<i>the power went out.</i>

17:04.100 --> 17:05.200
Mike:
<i>That's when one of them</i>

17:05.267 --> 17:07.734
<i>saw me and shot me.</i>

17:07.801 --> 17:10.167
I was screaming and something
in me told me like,

17:10.234 --> 17:13.901
"Shut up
or they might be coming,
looking for you."

17:13.968 --> 17:14.901
So I kept quiet

17:15.000 --> 17:17.534
<i>and I started running.</i>

17:17.601 --> 17:18.567
The minute
he got to us

17:18.634 --> 17:20.200
he collapsed,
he fell down.

17:20.267 --> 17:22.968
( woman gasps )
Oh, my God.

17:23.033 --> 17:24.601
( people chattering )

17:24.667 --> 17:26.100
To be honest,

17:26.167 --> 17:28.400
I've watched enough movies
to know what to do.

17:28.467 --> 17:30.467
( people chattering )

17:30.534 --> 17:32.601
Frank:
<i>When someone is shot</i>
<i>and they are bleeding,</i>

17:32.667 --> 17:36.367
<i>you have to apply pressure,
at least to stop the bleeding.</i>

17:37.467 --> 17:38.934
<i>I was a little bit scared</i>

17:39.000 --> 17:41.334
that he might succumb
to his wounds...

17:42.434 --> 17:44.801
but I didn't let that...

17:44.868 --> 17:47.400
distract me
from doing my best.

17:47.467 --> 17:49.334
To me, I feel that
telling him thank you--

17:49.400 --> 17:50.968
it's not enough.

17:51.033 --> 17:52.701
Yeah, 'cause he really
saved my life.

17:52.767 --> 17:55.634
♪ ♪

17:55.701 --> 17:57.367
Narrator:
<i>As the lights came back on,</i>

17:57.434 --> 17:59.534
<i>the first pair
of gunmen headed</i>

17:59.601 --> 18:03.367
<i>for the meat counter,
where 20 people were hiding.</i>

18:06.300 --> 18:08.133
I told the lady
that someone was coming,

18:08.200 --> 18:10.067
'cause I could
see the reflection
of someone coming.

18:11.901 --> 18:13.667
She was shaking and saying,
"They're coming.
They're coming."

18:13.734 --> 18:14.834
And I was like,
"Shh shh shh,"

18:14.901 --> 18:16.467
thinking they were
just gonna walk past.

18:16.534 --> 18:19.500
<i>But they came,
and they came straight
into where we were.</i>

18:20.634 --> 18:21.801
<i>And then,
very deliberately,</i>

18:21.868 --> 18:24.434
<i>they just shot
everybody around us.</i>

18:24.500 --> 18:27.033
I never looked up.
I never saw anything,

18:27.100 --> 18:29.534
but it was just
the sound of just...

18:29.601 --> 18:31.300
( mimics gunfire )

18:31.367 --> 18:33.434
♪ ♪

18:33.500 --> 18:36.167
Fred Bosire:
<i>They said, "Now it is</i>
<i>your turn.</i>"

18:36.234 --> 18:38.000
<i>We have come for you."</i>

18:39.133 --> 18:40.734
You know, as they
were shooting,

18:40.801 --> 18:43.067
children
were screaming.

18:43.133 --> 18:45.167
Yeah, as they
were shooting.

18:45.234 --> 18:46.200
I just felt
some pressure, though.

18:46.267 --> 18:47.634
I didn't really feel
any pain.

18:47.701 --> 18:49.868
It's now--
when the person walked away,

18:49.934 --> 18:52.367
I just looked
and I could see
that I'd been shot.

18:52.434 --> 18:54.901
And it was
a really strange
physical force,

18:55.000 --> 18:57.801
and I found out later that
I was shot in the--

18:57.868 --> 18:59.334
in my left leg.

18:59.400 --> 19:01.801
It entered in my left leg
and it came out by my right hip.

19:01.868 --> 19:04.067
♪ ♪

19:04.133 --> 19:06.267
<i>My main concern
at that point was
just to make sure</i>

19:06.334 --> 19:07.734
<i>that my kids
didn't see anything,</i>

19:07.801 --> 19:09.767
<i>just to try and get them
to keep their faces down.</i>

19:09.834 --> 19:11.567
<i>so I was holding
their faces down, saying,</i>

19:11.634 --> 19:13.167
<i>"Don't look up.
Don't look up."</i>

19:15.067 --> 19:16.467
There was
just a lot of blood

19:16.534 --> 19:19.234
and a lot of anguish
in people's faces

19:19.300 --> 19:20.901
as they lay there dying.

19:25.567 --> 19:27.033
Narrator:
<i>200 feet away,</i>

19:27.100 --> 19:29.367
<i>Katherine
and her three daughters</i>

19:29.434 --> 19:32.234
<i>were still hiding
under the display table.</i>

19:32.300 --> 19:34.934
Katherine:
<i>I was worried that my girls,</i>

19:35.000 --> 19:36.868
if they were to get shot--

19:36.934 --> 19:39.467
that I would have to lay there
and to watch them die,

19:39.534 --> 19:40.834
or if I were to be shot,

19:40.901 --> 19:42.567
that they would have to
lay there and watch me die.

19:42.634 --> 19:45.067
<i>And I didn't want them
to have to go through that.</i>

19:49.033 --> 19:50.701
Valentine:
<i>Where I was lying,</i>
<i>I could see</i>

19:50.767 --> 19:54.167
<i>there was this guy
at the doorway of Nakumatt,</i>

19:54.234 --> 19:57.200
and I asked him,
"What's going on?"

19:57.267 --> 20:00.167
And he told me, "Lie down."
That's what he told me.

20:00.234 --> 20:02.067
Because from there,
where he was,

20:02.133 --> 20:05.033
he could see
the other direction
where I could not see.

20:09.000 --> 20:10.400
Narrator:
<i>The second pair of gunmen</i>

20:10.467 --> 20:12.300
<i>had come down
from the rooftop.</i>

20:13.767 --> 20:15.634
<i>They shot anyone
they found.</i>

20:21.734 --> 20:24.534
Valentine:
<i>He was peeping, peeping.</i>

20:24.601 --> 20:28.534
<i>Why did he think of hiding
under the elephant?</i>

20:29.701 --> 20:32.300
<i>Anyone could see you.</i>

20:32.367 --> 20:35.334
Whenever I see that elephant,
for the rest of my life...

20:36.968 --> 20:38.868
I'll always remember
that guy.

20:38.934 --> 20:41.300
♪ ♪

20:59.968 --> 21:04.567
Narrator:
<i>Inside Nakumatt,</i>
<i>the four gunmen regrouped.</i>

21:04.634 --> 21:07.934
<i>They had murdered
several dozen people so far.</i>

21:08.033 --> 21:11.467
♪ ♪

21:11.534 --> 21:13.834
<i>Outside the mall,
there was still no sign</i>

21:13.901 --> 21:15.133
<i>of a rescue operation.</i>

21:15.200 --> 21:18.868
<i>It was 45 minutes
since the attack had begun.</i>

21:20.334 --> 21:21.567
Goran Tomasevic:
<i>I got a call of a friend,</i>

21:21.634 --> 21:23.667
<i>"and told me,
"Don't go to Westgate.
There's a robbery</i>

21:23.734 --> 21:25.300
<i>and there's lots
of dead people."</i>

21:25.367 --> 21:27.200
So I grab a camera
and drive down.

21:27.267 --> 21:29.133
( sirens approaching )

21:29.200 --> 21:30.467
♪ ♪
Narrator:
<i>Veteran war photographer</i>

21:30.534 --> 21:33.567
<i>Goran Tomasevic
of Reuters news agency</i>

21:33.634 --> 21:35.767
<i>shot rapid bursts
of pictures</i>

21:35.834 --> 21:38.167
<i>as he moved past
the terrorists' car</i>

21:38.234 --> 21:42.100
<i>and found the victims
of the first few minutes
of the attack.</i>

21:45.000 --> 21:47.934
Goran:
<i>Music coming out</i>
<i>of one of the bars.</i>

21:48.000 --> 21:49.968
It was very weird,
seeing dead people

21:50.033 --> 21:51.767
and some funny music
coming out.

21:51.834 --> 21:55.167
The kind of music
what you can hear
in elevators, you know?

21:55.234 --> 21:57.801
♪ ♪

21:57.868 --> 22:00.868
Narrator:
<i>A handful of police</i>
<i>had arrived,</i>

22:00.934 --> 22:02.367
<i>but the sound
of heavy gunfire</i>

22:02.434 --> 22:03.968
<i>had kept them
out of the mall.</i>

22:04.033 --> 22:06.267
♪ ♪

22:08.234 --> 22:12.000
<i>Amber lay behind
the meat counter
with her children,</i>

22:12.067 --> 22:14.467
<i>bleeding from a bullet
through the pelvis.</i>

22:15.634 --> 22:16.767
Amber:
<i>It felt endless.</i>

22:16.834 --> 22:18.500
<i>It felt like no one
was coming for us</i>

22:18.567 --> 22:20.234
<i>and I was
gonna die there.</i>

22:20.300 --> 22:21.734
<i>I was gonna die there
on top of my children,</i>

22:21.801 --> 22:23.634
<i>and what would happen
to them?</i>

22:25.067 --> 22:27.834
<i>The little boy next to me
was screaming in agony.</i>

22:27.901 --> 22:31.367
He'd been shot
and he was screaming,
"They've shot my mother!

22:31.434 --> 22:33.434
Why did this have to happen?
Why did they do this?"

22:33.500 --> 22:35.067
And screaming
and screaming,

22:35.133 --> 22:37.467
and I was trying
to calm him down.

22:38.901 --> 22:41.868
<i>At some point,
the sister also passed away.</i>

22:42.868 --> 22:43.734
The people
who were screaming

22:43.801 --> 22:45.500
stopped screaming,
eventually...

22:46.767 --> 22:50.167
as they died,
and so it became quieter.

22:52.234 --> 22:55.667
Narrator:
<i>Paul Muriuki, a driver</i>
<i>for an American charity,</i>

22:55.734 --> 22:57.434
<i>was still alive.</i>

22:57.500 --> 22:59.734
♪ ♪

23:10.434 --> 23:12.834
Esther Muriuki:
<i>He had seven gunshots.</i>

23:15.267 --> 23:16.667
They shoot him at once,

23:16.734 --> 23:18.901
and once they
realized that
he didn't die,

23:18.968 --> 23:21.500
they still come
and shoot him
once again.

23:21.567 --> 23:23.667
It was very painful.

23:25.033 --> 23:27.000
<i>He was a person
who loved dialogue</i>

23:27.067 --> 23:30.567
<i>to solve issues,
not violence.</i>

23:30.634 --> 23:32.667
<i>He was humble.</i>

23:32.734 --> 23:34.701
♪ ♪

23:37.033 --> 23:38.434
Narrator:
<i>In the burger restaurant,</i>

23:38.500 --> 23:40.334
<i>it had now been
50 minutes</i>

23:40.400 --> 23:42.868
<i>since Niall and his wife
had been shot.</i>

23:45.534 --> 23:47.767
Niall:
<i>Her legs had been</i>
<i>pretty badly shredded</i>

23:47.834 --> 23:51.634
<i>and she was losing
quite a lot of blood.</i>

23:52.868 --> 23:56.033
My shoulder and arm
had been very badly hit

23:56.100 --> 23:58.434
and I had, you know,

23:58.500 --> 24:00.534
holes big enough
to put fingers inside.

24:02.000 --> 24:04.601
<i>And with the blood
I was losing, myself,</i>

24:04.667 --> 24:07.167
<i>it was harder to stay
conscious the whole time.</i>

24:10.200 --> 24:12.267
She was clearly...

24:14.534 --> 24:17.734
on the edge and shaking

24:17.801 --> 24:21.067
from what must have been
blood loss, in retrospect.

24:23.000 --> 24:26.200
Clearly in a lot of pain.
Clearly very...

24:27.067 --> 24:28.534
very scared.

24:30.634 --> 24:33.200
I tried to move closer
to her at that point,

24:33.267 --> 24:35.801
took her hand
at one point.

24:36.868 --> 24:38.667
And...

24:41.234 --> 24:44.300
at some point, I'm...

24:45.267 --> 24:47.300
pretty sure she died.

24:47.367 --> 24:51.334
It was obviously
hard to tell but...

24:53.133 --> 24:55.367
I don't think
she was breathing.

25:02.868 --> 25:04.801
When I knew
I couldn't do anything else,

25:04.868 --> 25:06.601
I closed her eyes...

25:08.367 --> 25:11.567
took her wedding ring
so that it wouldn't get lost...

25:11.634 --> 25:13.667
and...

25:16.300 --> 25:18.133
just fell back.

25:22.467 --> 25:24.701
I think
I lay on her with...

25:24.767 --> 25:26.901
my head on her shoulder
for a little while,

25:26.968 --> 25:28.868
where I tried to get to
so that I could actually

25:28.934 --> 25:31.767
reach her
to do mouth-to-mouth, but...

25:32.734 --> 25:34.100
Yeah.

25:38.234 --> 25:39.801
I don't know.
I mean, after that,

25:39.868 --> 25:42.334
it felt fairly... empty.

25:42.400 --> 25:45.067
♪ ♪

25:49.701 --> 25:51.834
( ominous music playing )

25:56.100 --> 25:58.434
Amber:
<i>We then heard</i>
<i>the footsteps coming back,</i>

25:58.500 --> 26:01.033
<i>and the little boy
went quiet.</i>

26:01.100 --> 26:03.434
<i>He understood to play dead
at that point.</i>

26:06.734 --> 26:09.834
<i>"The terrorists asked--
"If there's children alive,
we'll let them go.</i>

26:09.901 --> 26:11.968
<i>We do not believe
in hurting children."</i>

26:13.033 --> 26:15.200
I don't know
where it came from,

26:15.267 --> 26:17.167
but I decided that,
probably, this was

26:17.234 --> 26:18.567
my only chance

26:18.634 --> 26:21.400
and the only chance
for my children,

26:21.467 --> 26:22.534
and so I stood up.

26:22.601 --> 26:24.300
♪ ♪

26:24.367 --> 26:26.634
<i>I said to him,
"My children are here.</i>

26:26.701 --> 26:29.367
<i>They're alive.
Will you let them go?"</i>

26:29.434 --> 26:30.634
He said, "Yes,
but you'll have to stay.

26:30.701 --> 26:33.567
The children can go,
but you'll have to stay."

26:33.634 --> 26:36.701
And so I started trying
to get my children
to stand up.

26:37.968 --> 26:39.334
Makena:
<i>I was expecting to hear him</i>

26:39.400 --> 26:40.734
<i>shooting them.</i>

26:40.801 --> 26:41.834
Then he asked,
"Who's Muslim?"

26:41.901 --> 26:43.534
And then
my friend's brother--

26:43.601 --> 26:46.033
he-- he--
I could hear him standing up.

26:46.100 --> 26:48.300
So he stood up
and then he said,
"I'm Muslim."

26:48.367 --> 26:51.434
<i>And he was like,
"You killed my mother
and my sister,</i>

26:51.500 --> 26:52.868
<i>and I love them very much."</i>

26:52.934 --> 26:55.033
<i>And he was like, "Sorry,
we are really really sorry.</i>

26:55.100 --> 26:57.901
<i>Please forgive us."</i>

26:57.968 --> 26:59.901
I started walking
with my children,

26:59.968 --> 27:01.367
kind of ignoring
the fact that he said

27:01.434 --> 27:02.634
that I would have to stay.

27:02.701 --> 27:05.901
<i>Then he said, "Can you take
the boy with you?"</i>

27:05.968 --> 27:07.801
<i>I asked the terrorist--
I said,</i>

27:07.868 --> 27:09.400
<i>"There's also
another girl here who's alive.</i>

27:09.467 --> 27:12.200
<i>Can I take her too?"
And he sort of looked at her.</i>

27:12.267 --> 27:15.100
<i>He didn't look best pleased,
but he said, "Okay."</i>

27:15.167 --> 27:16.968
I thought they were
up to something,

27:17.033 --> 27:18.901
because, I mean,
they were acting so nice,

27:18.968 --> 27:21.300
and these are the people
who have killed
so many people.

27:21.367 --> 27:24.200
Amber:
<i>'Cause I couldn't carry</i>
<i>the boy myself,</i>

27:24.267 --> 27:26.834
so I sort of just
threw him in the trolley.

27:26.901 --> 27:29.734
I remember my son
saying something to them.

27:29.801 --> 27:31.234
"It's not good
to shoot people.

27:31.300 --> 27:32.934
But it's not good
to shoot people.

27:33.000 --> 27:35.467
You're a bad man.
You've got to let
everybody go."

27:35.534 --> 27:38.467
And the man tried
to explain himself to them.

27:38.534 --> 27:42.300
<i>"Please forgive us."
And he was asking
for forgiveness.</i>

27:42.367 --> 27:44.467
And at that point
I said to my children,

27:44.534 --> 27:46.868
"Shut up.
Don't say another word.

27:46.934 --> 27:48.667
Be very quiet.
Just keep walking."

27:48.734 --> 27:50.901
And I just wanted
to just keep walking

27:50.968 --> 27:52.801
towards the exit.

27:52.868 --> 27:55.467
Makena:
<i>And he was like,</i>
<i>"Hey, and remember--"</i>

27:55.534 --> 27:57.067
<i>So I knew, "This is it."
So I just looked behind me,</i>

27:57.133 --> 27:58.701
<i>and then he said,
"Become Muslim."</i>

27:58.767 --> 28:00.334
<i>I said, "Yeah, yeah."</i>

28:00.400 --> 28:02.634
♪ ♪

28:06.567 --> 28:09.133
Katherine:
<i>We heard voices</i>
<i>of children.</i>

28:11.033 --> 28:13.767
<i>We looked at each other
and kind of questioned
what was going on,</i>

28:13.834 --> 28:16.334
<i>but there was a woman
that was with some children</i>

28:16.400 --> 28:19.133
<i>and she just walked out
of Nakumatt and left.</i>

28:20.267 --> 28:21.834
We thought maybe
she'd lost her mind.

28:21.901 --> 28:25.133
♪ ♪

28:25.200 --> 28:27.834
Amber:
<i>All you do is you focus</i>
<i>and it's one step at a time.</i>

28:27.901 --> 28:29.267
<i>One step, one breath,</i>

28:29.334 --> 28:32.300
<i>one step, one breath,
and just try to get out.</i>

28:32.367 --> 28:34.734
And yet my daughter was like
the complete opposite.

28:34.801 --> 28:38.200
She was just strolling along,
and I remember her saying,

28:38.267 --> 28:40.467
"Mommy, I don't want to do
any more shopping today."

28:50.534 --> 28:52.901
<i>The terrorists had actually
given them chocolate bars.</i>

28:52.968 --> 28:56.500
According to my daughter,
as they gave my son
the Mars bar,

28:56.567 --> 28:58.234
he said, "No,
can I have some chewing gum?"

28:58.300 --> 29:01.000
And Amelie said,
"No no, you've got
to take the Mars Bar."

29:01.067 --> 29:03.601
And you know,
it's like they were trying

29:03.667 --> 29:06.500
to-- to--
to appease the children,

29:06.567 --> 29:08.367
and explaining to them
what they were doing

29:08.434 --> 29:10.200
and why they were doing it,
and kept saying,

29:10.267 --> 29:12.133
"We're not monsters.
Here, have a chocolate."

29:12.200 --> 29:14.367
♪ ♪

29:23.634 --> 29:26.234
<i>I can't explain why
they asked for forgiveness,</i>

29:26.300 --> 29:27.868
<i>why they said
they were sorry.</i>

29:27.934 --> 29:30.601
I mean, you know,
how can you shoot
somebody one second,

29:30.667 --> 29:33.434
kill women and children,
and then say,

29:33.500 --> 29:35.167
"Oh, now we want
to let children go,"

29:35.234 --> 29:37.400
and then kill
more women and children

29:37.467 --> 29:39.300
and then say,
"Oh, but we're sorry?"

29:39.367 --> 29:41.500
You know,
how can you--

29:41.567 --> 29:44.767
it just shows how--
they're just mad.

29:44.834 --> 29:46.968
( sirens blaring )

29:48.734 --> 29:50.734
( chattering )

29:50.801 --> 29:52.167
She is injured--
behind her.

29:53.801 --> 29:55.234
What's your name?
What's your name?
( crying )

29:55.300 --> 29:56.500
What's your name?

29:58.167 --> 30:00.300
Narrator:
<i>90 minutes after</i>
<i>the attack had begun,</i>

30:00.367 --> 30:03.234
<i>the Kenyan security forces
still hadn't gone
into the mall.</i>

30:03.300 --> 30:04.667
Stay in the wall.
( chattering )

30:04.734 --> 30:06.167
Yeah, don't stand
in open area.

30:06.234 --> 30:07.868
Again, they fire.

30:07.934 --> 30:09.500
Stay on the wall.

30:09.567 --> 30:11.300
There's people dying up there,
bleeding to death,

30:11.367 --> 30:13.200
and I can't do
all 10 people on my own.

30:13.267 --> 30:14.701
Narrator:
<i>Some civilians had</i>
<i>been trying to get help</i>

30:14.767 --> 30:17.334
<i>to people injured
at the children's
cooking competition.</i>

30:17.400 --> 30:19.267
Give us time now
to go in with the SWAT.

30:19.334 --> 30:20.934
Man: Please,
I'm a soldier myself.

30:21.000 --> 30:22.467
You're a soldier,
but you are not a SWAT.

30:22.534 --> 30:24.701
I did 25--
And look upon me now,
we are here now.

30:24.767 --> 30:26.267
I did 25 years
in the army.
Give us time.

30:26.334 --> 30:27.934
Give us time!
I know a safe route.

30:28.000 --> 30:30.100
I'm telling you
our SWAT team is here.

30:30.167 --> 30:33.567
Give us time to
organize ourselves. Right?

30:33.634 --> 30:34.767
Men:
Yeah. Yes. Yes.

30:34.834 --> 30:35.901
Narrator:
<i>While the security forces</i>

30:36.000 --> 30:38.300
<i>debated what to do...</i>
No no, just walk.

30:38.367 --> 30:39.601
Please please
please please please.

30:39.667 --> 30:41.367
<i>...time was running out
for the wounded.</i>

30:41.434 --> 30:43.067
Man #2:
By the time you react,
people will die!

30:43.133 --> 30:44.701
♪ ♪

30:47.267 --> 30:49.467
Simon:
<i>Blood started spreading</i>
<i>all around me.</i>

30:50.934 --> 30:52.434
Well, how long now do I have

30:52.500 --> 30:54.701
before I just lose
too much blood?

30:54.767 --> 30:56.567
I could feel myself
getting a bit weaker,

30:56.634 --> 30:59.634
and I actually
mouthed to Amanda,
"I love you."

30:59.701 --> 31:01.601
Just-- I figured,

31:01.667 --> 31:04.901
"I've at least got a chance
to say something," right?

31:04.968 --> 31:06.467
We laid there
for a very long time

31:06.534 --> 31:10.734
and you would expect to see
a lot of armed soldiers

31:10.801 --> 31:13.033
and all just
coming up the ramp.

31:13.100 --> 31:15.968
Maybe that's what
we were expecting,
but that didn't happen.

31:16.033 --> 31:17.901
( chattering )

31:17.968 --> 31:20.000
Narrator:
<i>In the absence</i>
<i>of an official rescue plan,</i>

31:20.067 --> 31:22.467
<i>a handful
of plainclothes police</i>

31:22.534 --> 31:25.000
<i>decided to act
on their own.</i>

31:25.067 --> 31:27.300
We were very anxious

31:27.367 --> 31:30.334
to go in and see
if we can save
some lives.

31:30.400 --> 31:33.834
♪ ♪
Goran:<i> The police, they were</i>
<i>talking something in Swahili.</i>

31:33.901 --> 31:35.601
I did not-- I could not--
so I told them,

31:35.667 --> 31:38.567
"What you guys doing?"
They said, "We're going up."

31:38.634 --> 31:41.601
Narrator:
<i>Goran followed</i>
<i>Corporal Ali up the ramp.</i>

31:45.634 --> 31:48.567
Nura:
<i>I had harnessed</i>
<i>all pockets of courage</i>

31:48.634 --> 31:51.534
<i>that I had inside me
to come up there.</i>

31:51.601 --> 31:54.968
I was not thinking
that I could die,

31:55.033 --> 31:56.767
that I could get shot.

31:57.734 --> 31:59.500
I felt invincible.

32:00.367 --> 32:01.801
That's the truth.

32:01.868 --> 32:04.601
♪ ♪

32:04.667 --> 32:06.167
<i>At that stage,
I didn't even know</i>

32:06.234 --> 32:09.100
<i>that there were
people up there.</i>

32:21.467 --> 32:23.367
I felt very angry.

32:26.200 --> 32:28.100
I felt disgusted...

32:29.367 --> 32:32.000
with the wanton killing
that took place there.

32:33.901 --> 32:37.200
<i>In my line of duty,
I have never shed tears.</i>

32:37.267 --> 32:41.367
On that day,
I found tears...

32:42.767 --> 32:44.467
dropping from my eyes.

32:44.534 --> 32:46.267
♪ ♪

32:46.334 --> 32:51.000
<i>I just ran down
like a crazy man.</i>

32:51.067 --> 32:53.601
"We need ambulance!
We need ambulance!"

32:53.667 --> 32:55.000
( indiscernible dialog )

32:55.067 --> 32:57.234
Stretcher!
Stretcher, please!
Stretcher here!

32:57.300 --> 32:58.400
Stay with us!

32:58.467 --> 33:01.534
( indiscernible dialog )

33:01.601 --> 33:06.033
( girl screams )
My friend!

33:06.100 --> 33:07.634
Narrator:
<i>Simon Belcher had</i>
<i>been bleeding</i>

33:07.701 --> 33:10.100
<i>for two hours
by the time help came.</i>

33:10.167 --> 33:12.067
My survival depended

33:12.133 --> 33:14.133
on getting
to hospital A.S.A.P.

33:15.334 --> 33:18.500
<i>My doctor said
another 10-15 minutes</i>

33:18.567 --> 33:20.300
<i>and I would have gone.</i>

33:21.367 --> 33:22.734
Narrator:
<i>Ruhila Adatia,</i>

33:22.801 --> 33:25.300
<i>a popular radio host,
was seven months pregnant.</i>

33:25.367 --> 33:27.901
<i>She had been shot
in the leg.</i>

33:27.968 --> 33:30.367
Issa Premji:
<i>I went straight for Ruhila</i>

33:30.434 --> 33:31.934
and she opened
her eyes and she
told me,

33:32.000 --> 33:33.200
"Issa, help me."

33:33.267 --> 33:34.734
I said,
"No, I'm here.

33:34.801 --> 33:36.167
I'm getting you
out of here."

33:36.234 --> 33:38.634
( chatter )
Move! Move!

33:38.701 --> 33:40.767
Issa:
<i>When we picked her up,</i>

33:40.834 --> 33:42.133
she was still
talking to me.

33:42.200 --> 33:45.100
When I put her
in the ambulance, right,

33:45.167 --> 33:47.100
her eyes rolled back...

33:48.434 --> 33:49.734
and I straight away
told the guy,

33:49.801 --> 33:51.567
"She's going into shock."

33:53.267 --> 33:55.133
Narrator:
<i>Ruhila and her unborn child</i>

33:55.200 --> 33:57.834
<i>died on the way
to a hospital.</i>

34:00.000 --> 34:02.267
Ruhila, that we lost,
she was a Muslim.

34:02.334 --> 34:05.901
She was expecting
a baby of her faith,

34:05.968 --> 34:07.801
so it did not matter.

34:07.868 --> 34:09.801
It just did not
matter to them.

34:09.868 --> 34:11.767
Whatever it is,

34:11.834 --> 34:14.033
Let the ambulance crew
move out with them!

34:14.100 --> 34:16.500
You need to get out!
Man: Yeah,
ambulance, ambulance!

34:17.701 --> 34:18.801
Narrator:
<i>A handful of civilians</i>

34:18.868 --> 34:20.100
<i>had come to the rooftop</i>

34:20.167 --> 34:22.968
<i>to assist the Red Cross
and the plainclothes police.</i>

34:23.033 --> 34:24.901
( chattering )

34:24.968 --> 34:27.033
Abdul Haji:
<i>We saw the level of destruction</i>

34:27.100 --> 34:29.334
that had taken place--
the murder and the killing

34:29.400 --> 34:31.500
and the injured
people.

34:31.567 --> 34:33.868
And we knew
there were
survivors in there.

34:35.467 --> 34:37.534
Harish Patel:
<i>We just said,</i>
<i>"Whoever has the balls,</i>

34:37.601 --> 34:40.400
<i>we go in.
The rest stay."</i>

34:40.467 --> 34:42.167
( speaks Swahili )

34:42.234 --> 34:44.400
"If we have
to die, we die."

34:44.467 --> 34:46.300
♪ ♪

34:47.634 --> 34:50.400
Narrator:
<i>Now seven men</i>
<i>went into the mall:</i>

34:50.467 --> 34:52.200
<i>five plainclothes police</i>

34:52.267 --> 34:54.634
<i>and civilians
Harish and Abdul</i>

34:54.701 --> 34:57.300
<i>who were carrying
licensed handguns.</i>

35:01.133 --> 35:03.267
Abdul:
<i>We didn't have</i>
<i>a command structure.</i>

35:03.334 --> 35:05.467
<i>We were not
taking orders from anybody.</i>

35:06.801 --> 35:08.500
Most of the police
were still outside,

35:08.567 --> 35:11.133
But we did have
the plainclothes police officers

35:11.200 --> 35:12.734
who were with us inside.

35:12.801 --> 35:15.033
♪ ♪

35:22.400 --> 35:25.667
Nura:
<i>When we hit</i>
<i>the ground floor now...</i>

35:25.734 --> 35:28.934
hey, bullets started
flying now.

35:29.000 --> 35:31.734
Those guys,
they started showing us

35:31.801 --> 35:34.334
<i>that they really
meant business.</i>

35:35.601 --> 35:37.767
Goran:
<i>I clearly saw</i>
<i>one of the gunmens.</i>

35:37.834 --> 35:40.834
<i>"Shall I do picture?"
Then I said, "No,
because it-it-it--</i>

35:40.901 --> 35:42.667
<i>it smells bad."</i>

35:42.734 --> 35:44.300
I said to police,
"We have to be careful.

35:44.367 --> 35:46.234
We can get shot."

35:48.534 --> 35:50.200
Abdul:
<i>I had 14 rounds,</i>

35:50.267 --> 35:51.934
<i>and it didn't
quite cross our mind</i>

35:52.000 --> 35:54.801
<i>that we had small guns
and they had big guns.</i>

35:54.868 --> 35:57.367
A gun is a gun.
At the end of the day,
it's how good you are with it.

35:57.434 --> 36:00.334
Narrator:
<i>The display table</i>
<i>opposite the entrance</i>

36:00.400 --> 36:02.968
<i>to Nakumatt was now
in the crossfire.</i>

36:03.033 --> 36:07.868
It was instantaneous fear
and just dread.

36:09.567 --> 36:11.734
Valentine:
<i>The bullets, they're shining.</i>

36:11.801 --> 36:13.834
<i>( mimics gunfire )</i>

36:13.901 --> 36:17.500
<i>I felt a big bang
on my leg.</i>

36:18.400 --> 36:19.868
I knew I was shot.

36:19.934 --> 36:22.767
I really tried
to look like this,

36:22.834 --> 36:24.167
down like this,

36:24.234 --> 36:27.200
then I saw a hole
in my jeans...

36:27.267 --> 36:29.667
into my flesh.

36:29.734 --> 36:31.868
( ominous music playing )

36:33.300 --> 36:37.334
Nura:
<i>I felt a heavy punch</i>
<i>in my back.</i>

36:37.400 --> 36:39.801
<i>I realized that
the punch was a bullet.</i>

36:39.868 --> 36:41.934
<i>I've been shot.</i>

36:43.267 --> 36:46.267
<i>With the effort
that I was making,</i>

36:46.334 --> 36:48.267
I released the grip

36:48.334 --> 36:50.234
that I had on the...

36:50.300 --> 36:53.767
the torn abdomen...

36:54.801 --> 36:58.334
and I found
the intestines,

36:58.400 --> 37:00.467
bubbling out.

37:02.234 --> 37:05.434
<i>Goran came
and lifted me up.</i>

37:06.434 --> 37:07.734
When I was running
with him,

37:07.801 --> 37:09.767
he start firing
his AK by accident

37:09.834 --> 37:11.133
between our legs,

37:11.200 --> 37:12.834
so it was
little bit difficult.

37:14.767 --> 37:16.667
<i>He was
a very brave guy.</i>

37:16.734 --> 37:18.767
<i>I heard after
he was all right.</i>

37:18.834 --> 37:21.467
( indiscernible shouting )

37:21.534 --> 37:23.334
( gunshot )

37:23.400 --> 37:25.734
Let's go!
( indiscernible shouting )

37:25.801 --> 37:28.234
Get an ambulance, please!
Get an ambulance!

37:28.300 --> 37:31.234
( indiscernible dialog )

37:34.467 --> 37:37.133
Narrator:
<i>As the gun battle</i>
<i>raged inside the mall,</i>

37:37.200 --> 37:41.734
<i>the police SWAT team was
outside waiting for orders.</i>

37:45.868 --> 37:47.234
Abdul:
<i>If there was any time</i>

37:47.300 --> 37:49.334
<i>that any of us
should have run away,</i>

37:49.400 --> 37:51.634
<i>it was when
our colleague was shot.</i>

37:51.701 --> 37:54.701
At that point in time,
if there was any coward
amongst us,

37:54.767 --> 37:56.868
he would have--
he would have opted out

37:56.934 --> 37:59.234
and left.
But nobody left.

37:59.300 --> 38:01.467
♪ ♪

38:01.534 --> 38:04.334
Narrator:
<i>By engaging the terrorists</i>
<i>at the front of Nakumatt,</i>

38:04.400 --> 38:06.634
<i>Abdul and his group enabled</i>

38:06.701 --> 38:09.701
<i>more than a hundred
trapped civilians to escape,</i>

38:09.767 --> 38:11.500
<i>including Katherine's sons.</i>

38:11.567 --> 38:15.300
Blaise:
<i>We asked, "Is our mother out?</i>
<i>Is she safe?"</i>

38:15.367 --> 38:20.167
<i>They responded,
"We don't know. Just pray."</i>

38:20.234 --> 38:21.767
We really had
no clue where she was,

38:21.834 --> 38:25.534
but we knew she was inside
Westgate somewhere.

38:26.934 --> 38:28.534
Abdul:
<i>We noticed that there was--</i>

38:28.601 --> 38:31.334
<i>there was a lady
hiding under a table</i>

38:31.400 --> 38:34.133
<i>and she looked terrified.</i>

38:35.767 --> 38:38.868
Katherine:
<i>The Kenyan lady finally said,</i>
<i>"The cops are here."</i>

38:38.934 --> 38:41.767
I couldn't see them,
but the other ladies could,

38:41.834 --> 38:43.367
and they were
communicating with them.

38:43.434 --> 38:45.000
♪ ♪

38:45.067 --> 38:47.968
We were quite shocked
because she was right
in the middle

38:48.033 --> 38:51.801
of the crossfire
between the gunmen and us.

38:54.567 --> 38:57.801
<i>I signaled
to my colleagues,</i>

38:57.868 --> 39:00.200
I told them,
"There's a lady.

39:00.267 --> 39:03.968
She's in a bad situation.
We need to get her out."

39:06.634 --> 39:10.834
<i>At one point this guy
with a black bandanna
tied on his head--</i>

39:10.901 --> 39:15.968
<i>my eyes and his locked,
and he was taunting me.</i>

39:17.834 --> 39:19.367
He was saying...
( speaks Swahili )

39:19.434 --> 39:20.534
You know, "Come, come!"

39:20.601 --> 39:22.834
<i>He was taunting us
to come closer</i>

39:22.901 --> 39:25.567
<i>so that we can engage
in a fight.</i>

39:27.901 --> 39:30.367
<i>I'm a Kenyan-Somali,
a Muslim.</i>

39:30.434 --> 39:32.734
What angered me the most

39:32.801 --> 39:35.100
was the fact
that they were Muslims...

39:36.133 --> 39:38.033
and they were
purporting to...

39:38.100 --> 39:39.968
do whatever they were doing
in the name of Islam.

39:40.033 --> 39:42.200
♪ ♪

39:42.267 --> 39:45.067
Narrator:
<i>One of the plainclothes</i>
<i>policemen threw tear gas,</i>

39:45.133 --> 39:48.701
<i>hoping to push the terrorists
further back into Nakumatt.</i>

40:02.100 --> 40:04.200
Abdul:
<i>We started proceeding</i>
<i>closer and closer</i>

40:04.267 --> 40:06.701
<i>towards
the supermarket entrance.</i>

40:09.601 --> 40:11.767
Narrator:
<i>Diagonally opposite</i>
<i>the display table</i>

40:11.834 --> 40:13.667
<i>was a pharmacy.</i>

40:14.801 --> 40:16.367
<i>We were much closer
to the lady</i>

40:16.434 --> 40:17.601
<i>who was hiding
under the table.</i>

40:17.667 --> 40:19.067
<i>We were able
to communicate with her...</i>

40:20.200 --> 40:22.033
<i>so we told her to run,</i>

40:22.100 --> 40:23.868
<i>and she shook her head.</i>

40:25.467 --> 40:27.434
I told him
that I can't come,

40:27.500 --> 40:30.901
because we are four ladies
and three kids there.

40:33.500 --> 40:36.067
Narrator:
<i>As Abdul prepared</i>
<i>to rescue the women,</i>

40:36.133 --> 40:37.934
<i>he found
another group of people</i>

40:38.000 --> 40:39.434
<i>hiding in the pharmacy.</i>

40:39.500 --> 40:42.200
♪ ♪

40:44.400 --> 40:45.901
<i>He now had only minutes</i>

40:45.968 --> 40:47.667
<i>to get them all to safety</i>

40:47.734 --> 40:49.601
<i>before the terrorists
could recover</i>

40:49.667 --> 40:52.467
<i>from the tear gas
and open fire again.</i>

40:52.534 --> 40:55.667
♪ ♪

41:12.534 --> 41:15.601
Katherine:
<i>One of the Asian ladies</i>
<i>reached out her hands</i>

41:15.667 --> 41:18.234
and signaled that she would
carry the baby for me.

41:19.367 --> 41:21.167
Diljeet:
<i>I told that lady,</i>

41:21.234 --> 41:23.234
"Just give me
your small baby,"

41:23.300 --> 41:26.033
so-- I know that
she can't run with three kids.

41:27.467 --> 41:29.467
Katherine:
<i>So I handed her Petra,</i>

41:29.534 --> 41:31.434
'cause I knew by then
my legs were jelly

41:31.500 --> 41:33.868
and I just wouldn't be able
to carry all of them.

41:33.934 --> 41:37.667
Valentine:
<i>They told us,</i>
<i>"You go one by one."</i>

41:37.734 --> 41:40.133
I prayed my last prayers,
then I decided "No."

41:40.200 --> 41:41.601
I told God,
"I'm not dying today."

41:41.667 --> 41:44.200
( laughs )
"No no, not today!"

41:58.634 --> 41:59.968
Katherine:
<i>She just knew.</i>

42:00.033 --> 42:01.767
<i>She just knew it was
her opportunity to go,</i>

42:01.834 --> 42:03.934
<i>and so she ran.</i>

42:08.701 --> 42:10.667
Valentine:
<i>She was very brave.</i>

42:10.734 --> 42:12.400
Very brave.

42:12.467 --> 42:14.701
♪ ♪

42:41.767 --> 42:45.868
Katherine:
<i>Almost the entire time</i>
<i>my mind was on getting out,</i>

42:45.934 --> 42:48.334
<i>and when I would get out,
and what would happen</i>

42:48.400 --> 42:51.500
<i>when I got out,
and what I would do
the rest of the day.</i>

42:51.567 --> 42:53.868
And I kept thinking,
"How am I supposed
to drive home?

42:53.934 --> 42:55.601
My nerves are
completely shot.

42:55.667 --> 42:58.133
There's just no way
that I'm gonna be able
to drive home."

42:58.200 --> 42:59.968
( chattering )

43:00.033 --> 43:01.667
Katherine:
<i>It was wonderful.</i>

43:01.734 --> 43:03.400
<i>We know that
it was a miracle.</i>

43:03.467 --> 43:06.200
( chattering )

43:06.267 --> 43:08.000
Okay.
Move, move, move.

43:09.334 --> 43:11.133
Valentine:
<i>There were just four of us.</i>

43:11.200 --> 43:13.500
<i>Everybody was close
to each other.</i>

43:13.567 --> 43:15.300
<i>We don't know each other.</i>

43:15.367 --> 43:17.267
<i>We all come
from different communities,</i>

43:17.334 --> 43:20.601
<i>but at that time
we were one.</i>

43:21.834 --> 43:23.033
I'll always treasure
that moment,

43:23.100 --> 43:25.767
because everybody was
caring about the other.

43:25.834 --> 43:27.801
♪ ♪

43:30.200 --> 43:32.234
Narrator:
<i>Having been forced</i>
<i>to the back</i>

43:32.300 --> 43:33.734
<i>of the supermarket
by the tear gas,</i>

43:33.801 --> 43:36.100
<i>the gunmen were
now just feet away</i>

43:36.167 --> 43:38.400
<i>from Margie
and her baby.</i>

43:41.434 --> 43:44.334
Margie:
<i>I was thinking, "I've got</i>
<i>to slow my breath down,</i>

43:44.400 --> 43:46.400
'cause this baby is
gonna pick up

43:46.467 --> 43:49.400
on the kind of extreme fear
that I'm feeling right now."

43:49.467 --> 43:51.200
<i>I was almost
just counting the seconds,</i>

43:51.267 --> 43:53.667
<i>every single second
that passed.</i>

43:53.734 --> 43:56.367
<i>And all of a sudden
it happened.</i>

43:56.434 --> 43:58.133
<i>There he was.</i>

43:58.200 --> 44:00.701
I looked up at him
and I just mouthed the words,

44:00.767 --> 44:05.200
"He's just a baby.
He's just a baby.

44:05.267 --> 44:07.033
He's just a baby."

44:07.100 --> 44:09.000
And I must have said it
quite a few times,

44:09.067 --> 44:11.100
and he just
kept on staring at me.

44:11.167 --> 44:13.100
And after a while,
he looked to the side

44:13.167 --> 44:16.167
at some of his colleagues
that were there

44:16.234 --> 44:19.400
and said something
in a language that
I didn't understand.

44:19.467 --> 44:22.267
And someone
in a broken voice said,

44:22.334 --> 44:25.167
"Lady with baby,
stand up!"

44:27.100 --> 44:28.734
<i>Then as
I'm looking at them,</i>

44:28.801 --> 44:32.367
the terrorist
that's in the middle
in the front looks at us,

44:32.434 --> 44:34.300
sees the baby
peering around,

44:34.367 --> 44:36.167
turns his head
to the side,

44:36.234 --> 44:39.500
kinda cocks his head,
makes this cute baby face
and goes...

44:39.567 --> 44:42.868
and waves at me
and waves at the baby like...

44:43.901 --> 44:45.334
And I just
remember thinking,

44:45.400 --> 44:47.367
"If they see my face now,

44:47.434 --> 44:49.734
they're gonna know
how crazy I think this is.

44:49.801 --> 44:51.601
I can't believe
what just happened.

44:51.667 --> 44:53.334
They're killing
women and children

44:53.400 --> 44:56.500
"and they're making
baby faces at us and waving."

44:58.133 --> 45:01.334
<i>So I turned around
and started walking out.</i>

45:03.100 --> 45:07.534
<i>As I got there,
this tear gas dropped
right at the entrance.</i>

45:08.767 --> 45:10.334
<i>I had to decide:</i>

45:10.400 --> 45:14.100
<i>do I walk out
into the mall area
from the supermarket</i>

45:14.167 --> 45:17.634
"or do I turn around
and go back into
the supermarket?"

45:17.701 --> 45:19.467
I was like,
"I'm not going back
to where those guys are.

45:19.534 --> 45:21.300
I'm not going back
to where they just
killed everybody."

45:21.367 --> 45:24.601
♪ ♪

45:43.167 --> 45:44.667
<i>There were
hordes of people.</i>

45:44.734 --> 45:46.801
<i>There were security
forces outside.</i>

45:46.868 --> 45:49.901
I mean it felt
like millions of people
had surrounded the mall.

45:49.968 --> 45:52.601
<i>And I didn't stop.
I just kept on running.</i>

45:52.667 --> 45:56.133
♪ ♪

45:56.200 --> 45:58.601
Abdul:
<i>The tear gas had</i>
<i>actually affected my eyes,</i>

45:58.667 --> 46:03.601
<i>so I started walking
towards the main entrance.</i>

46:03.667 --> 46:07.467
On the right side there was
the Urban Burger café,

46:07.534 --> 46:10.167
so I thought I might
as well get some water

46:10.234 --> 46:12.167
and splash it in my face.

46:13.534 --> 46:15.133
Narrator:
<i>By now Niall</i>
<i>had been bleeding</i>

46:15.200 --> 46:17.934
<i>for more
than 3 hours.</i>

46:18.000 --> 46:20.367
Niall:<i> I'd lay there,</i>
<i>kind of drifting in and out</i>
<i>of consciousness</i>

46:20.434 --> 46:21.968
<i>and at some point
I was aware of movement</i>

46:22.033 --> 46:24.467
<i>coming into
the burger restaurant.</i>

46:24.534 --> 46:26.801
Someone had come over...

46:26.868 --> 46:29.868
and was basically
washing their--

46:29.934 --> 46:31.567
their face and eyes
in the sink

46:31.634 --> 46:34.167
that was more or less
above our heads.

46:35.634 --> 46:37.534
Abdul:
<i>I asked him</i>
<i>where he'd been injured</i>

46:37.601 --> 46:40.400
<i>and he pointed
to his shoulder and his leg.</i>

46:40.467 --> 46:44.200
So I told him...
"Just bear with me.

46:44.267 --> 46:46.067
I'm going to get
some help for you,

46:46.133 --> 46:47.801
and we'll get you
out of here."

46:50.434 --> 46:53.133
Niall:
<i>You try and do what</i>
<i>you can not to be helpless,</i>

46:53.200 --> 46:56.133
<i>but when that kind
of situation happens,</i>

46:56.200 --> 46:58.367
<i>there's a limited set
of options.</i>

46:58.434 --> 47:01.400
<i>The biggest thing is
not knowing what's happening,</i>

47:01.467 --> 47:03.801
<i>and so you're having
to make choices</i>

47:03.868 --> 47:06.300
<i>without any real idea</i>

47:06.367 --> 47:09.067
<i>of what the consequences
of those choices could be.</i>

47:09.133 --> 47:10.934
It feels wrong in some ways
calling it "unlucky,"

47:11.000 --> 47:13.033
because someone set out
to do this.

47:13.100 --> 47:15.868
But for us to be there...

47:17.100 --> 47:19.267
was just a matter
of bad luck.

47:19.334 --> 47:24.100
♪ ♪
( indiscernible dialog )

47:24.167 --> 47:26.133
Narrator:
<i>Pablo Ghataurhae</i>
<i>had gone to watch</i>

47:26.200 --> 47:28.334
<i>the cooking competition
with his family.</i>

47:30.033 --> 47:31.133
<i>When the attack began,</i>

47:31.200 --> 47:34.033
<i>he was on the rooftop
with his grandmother.</i>

47:35.067 --> 47:37.367
Dipi Ghataurhae:
<i>Pablo was 17 years old.</i>

47:37.434 --> 47:39.500
<i>He was going
to go into university</i>

47:39.567 --> 47:41.534
<i>to do mechanical engineering.</i>

47:41.601 --> 47:42.934
♪ ♪

47:43.000 --> 47:45.400
<i>He wanted
to be a rally driver.</i>

47:47.400 --> 47:48.801
It's funny,
he used to make

47:48.868 --> 47:51.734
these statements
to me at times,

47:51.801 --> 47:54.634
"When I become
a rally driver..."

47:55.834 --> 47:57.534
be prepared, Mom.

47:57.601 --> 48:00.634
I'm gonna die early...

48:02.500 --> 48:04.534
"so you be prepared."

48:06.334 --> 48:10.200
<i>He went with his grandma,
which I'm proud of.</i>

48:11.400 --> 48:13.467
He looked after her
while she was alive,

48:13.534 --> 48:16.634
and he's looking after her
all the way up there.

48:21.567 --> 48:23.968
♪ ♪

48:24.033 --> 48:25.701
Narrator:
<i>The terrorists returned</i>
<i>to the meat counter,</i>

48:25.767 --> 48:30.100
<i>looking for anyone
hiding or playing dead.</i>

48:30.167 --> 48:33.667
There is a lady
who was behind me.

48:34.634 --> 48:36.834
She-- she was alive.

48:36.901 --> 48:40.834
Narrator:
<i>The gunmen had been speaking</i>
<i>to their masters in Somalia</i>

48:40.901 --> 48:43.500
<i>and needed more minutes
for their cell phones.</i>

48:43.567 --> 48:45.734
Edwin Omoding:
<i>They're saying,</i>

48:45.801 --> 48:49.000
<i>"Where do we find
the Safaricom scratch cards?"</i>

48:49.067 --> 48:50.634
So the lady
said,

48:50.701 --> 48:52.300
"The scratch
cards--

48:52.367 --> 48:54.434
it is
at the tills,

48:54.500 --> 48:59.167
but I don't know
the password."

49:01.100 --> 49:04.133
Jared Odhiambo:
<i>After that they ask her,</i>
<i>"Are you a Kenyan?"</i>

49:04.200 --> 49:05.300
The lady
say yeah,

49:05.367 --> 49:07.667
she's
a Kenyan.

49:07.734 --> 49:09.100
They ask her
if she's

49:09.167 --> 49:11.100
a Christian
or a Muslim.

49:11.167 --> 49:14.033
The lady told them,
"I'm a Christian."

49:15.367 --> 49:16.801
<i>One of them just fired.</i>

49:16.868 --> 49:21.300
One gunshot
and the lady was dead.

49:23.467 --> 49:25.400
Narrator:
<i>Cashier Veronicah Kamau</i>

49:25.467 --> 49:27.701
<i>was killed
at nine minutes to 4:00,</i>

49:27.767 --> 49:30.934
<i>three hours and 21 minutes
into the attack.</i>

49:32.334 --> 49:34.968
<i>She was the last civilian
to die at Westgate.</i>

49:38.400 --> 49:40.634
♪ ♪

49:50.701 --> 49:52.968
<i>The terrorists
left the shop floor</i>

49:53.033 --> 49:55.000
<i>and headed up
a service staircase</i>

49:55.067 --> 49:56.934
<i>towards
the furniture storeroom.</i>

50:01.500 --> 50:04.601
<i>Of perhaps 2,000 people
at the mall that Saturday,</i>

50:04.667 --> 50:06.567
<i>they had killed 61,</i>

50:06.634 --> 50:09.534
<i>including a dozen children
and three pregnant women.</i>

50:09.601 --> 50:13.467
<i>Hundreds more were left
with permanent injuries.</i>

50:18.434 --> 50:20.234
( chattering )

50:24.200 --> 50:26.667
<i>Three and a half hours after
the terrorists had struck,</i>

50:26.734 --> 50:30.500
<i>the police SWAT team
finally entered the mall,</i>

50:30.567 --> 50:33.133
<i>but it was
too late to save anyone.</i>

50:33.200 --> 50:35.067
<i>The massacre was over.</i>

50:35.133 --> 50:37.634
♪ ♪

50:37.701 --> 50:40.234
<i>As they worked their way down
from the second floor...</i>

50:41.767 --> 50:43.801
<i>on the ground floor
a platoon of Kenyan soldiers</i>

50:43.868 --> 50:47.300
<i>were entering Nakumatt,
looking for the terrorists.</i>

50:47.367 --> 50:51.834
♪ ♪

50:51.901 --> 50:54.367
Narrator:
<i>They advanced through</i>
<i>the vegetable section</i>

50:54.434 --> 50:56.133
<i>towards the meat counter,</i>

50:56.200 --> 50:58.500
<i>where six shop workers
were still hiding.</i>

50:58.567 --> 51:00.968
♪ ♪

51:01.033 --> 51:03.934
We can see them,
on that reflection.

51:04.000 --> 51:05.767
I told--

51:05.834 --> 51:07.934
I told my
friend, "Hey,

51:08.000 --> 51:09.934
is that police?
Are they police?"

51:10.033 --> 51:11.667
I opened the door.

51:11.734 --> 51:13.334
They felt
I was a terrorist,

51:13.400 --> 51:16.067
so they sprayed the bullets
towards that side.

51:17.133 --> 51:18.434
Narrator:
<i>The soldiers now fired</i>

51:18.500 --> 51:20.434
<i>at anything that moved.</i>

51:21.367 --> 51:23.100
I tried
to signal at them,

51:23.167 --> 51:24.767
as I waved the uniform.

51:24.834 --> 51:27.033
"We are the Nakumatt staff!
Nakumatt staff!"

51:27.100 --> 51:30.367
Because I felt
it was unsafe just
to come out physically,

51:30.434 --> 51:32.167
that one--
they would have shot me.

51:32.234 --> 51:34.767
Man, those soldiers--
they do not consider.

51:34.834 --> 51:37.133
They are just shooting, yeah?
They're just shooting.

51:38.901 --> 51:40.868
Narrator:
<i>As the soldiers fired</i>
<i>wildly around them,</i>

51:40.934 --> 51:42.868
<i>the four terrorists
were relaxing</i>

51:42.934 --> 51:44.667
<i>in the furniture storeroom.</i>

51:46.234 --> 51:48.367
( rattling )

51:49.968 --> 51:53.000
Narrator:
<i>By mistake,</i>
<i>the army shot three policemen,</i>

51:53.067 --> 51:55.300
<i>one of them fatally.</i>

51:58.801 --> 52:02.367
Issa:
<i>We put him onto the stretcher</i>
<i>and we were rushing him out,</i>

52:02.434 --> 52:05.868
<i>then all of a sudden
he started shaking.</i>

52:06.968 --> 52:09.400
( speaks English )

52:09.467 --> 52:11.133
( chattering )

52:11.200 --> 52:12.901
He clearly said,
"We can't work like this.

52:12.968 --> 52:16.500
We are the ones who
are supposed to be
the head of this."

52:18.367 --> 52:20.367
<i>They withdrew completely
from the operation.</i>

52:24.500 --> 52:26.801
Narrator:
<i>In the confusion,</i>
<i>both the Kenyan army</i>

52:26.868 --> 52:29.534
<i>and the police SWAT team
left the mall,</i>

52:29.601 --> 52:32.133
<i>just 90 minutes
after they'd arrived.</i>

52:32.200 --> 52:34.434
♪ ♪

52:41.467 --> 52:43.667
Narrator:
<i>In the furniture storeroom,</i>

52:43.734 --> 52:46.400
<i>the al-Shabaab gunmen prayed.</i>

52:48.133 --> 52:50.367
<i>They had come to kill
and be killed.</i>

52:50.434 --> 52:54.400
<i>Now they waited
for the Kenyans to attack.</i>

53:00.167 --> 53:02.567
<i>Very little
is known about them.</i>

53:02.634 --> 53:06.534
<i>The youngest was 19,
the oldest 23.</i>

53:07.934 --> 53:11.067
<i>All four had arrived
in Kenya three months earlier.</i>

53:11.133 --> 53:15.367
<i>They had scouted Westgate
a number of times
before the attack.</i>

53:26.200 --> 53:28.133
<i>After a few hours
in the storeroom,</i>

53:28.200 --> 53:30.868
<i>the terrorists noticed
the security camera</i>

53:30.934 --> 53:33.267
<i>and disconnected it.</i>

53:36.434 --> 53:39.767
<i>Later that night,
a squad of Kenyan soldiers</i>

53:39.834 --> 53:41.934
<i>crept back
into Nakumatt.</i>

53:43.300 --> 53:44.567
<i>With them was
a civilian</i>

53:44.634 --> 53:46.400
<i>who videoed
the meat counter</i>

53:46.467 --> 53:47.734
<i>where Amber
and her children</i>

53:47.801 --> 53:50.033
<i>had hidden
earlier in the day.</i>

53:50.100 --> 53:52.534
♪ ♪

54:01.500 --> 54:03.300
<i>Fred Bosire,
in his white coat,</i>

54:03.367 --> 54:06.567
<i>had been playing dead
for 8 hours.</i>

54:06.634 --> 54:08.801
Fred:
<i>I still lied down.</i>

54:08.868 --> 54:11.100
When I saw
the military boots

54:11.167 --> 54:15.000
and the uniform,
now I was relieved.

54:15.067 --> 54:17.067
( speaking foreign language )

54:18.467 --> 54:20.067
Narrator:
<i>The shop workers</i>
<i>who'd been hiding</i>

54:20.133 --> 54:23.033
<i>behind the meat locker
were also freed.</i>

54:24.334 --> 54:25.500
<i>They were the last group
of civilians</i>

54:25.567 --> 54:26.934
<i>to be rescued
from the mall.</i>

54:27.000 --> 54:29.300
♪ ♪

54:29.367 --> 54:31.934
I was very lucky.
I can say I was very lucky.

54:32.000 --> 54:35.234
Maybe that was my day.
That's what I can say.

54:43.901 --> 54:46.033
Narrator:
<i>At 13 minutes past 9:00,</i>

54:46.100 --> 54:47.567
<i>a security camera captured</i>

54:47.634 --> 54:50.167
<i>the last recorded image
of the terrorists.</i>

54:50.234 --> 54:52.434
♪ ♪

55:05.367 --> 55:06.868
Narrator:
<i>The stand-off</i>
<i>between the terrorists</i>

55:06.934 --> 55:10.300
<i>and the Kenyan army
continued for another 40 hours,</i>

55:10.367 --> 55:13.667
<i>during which
five soldiers were killed.</i>

55:17.634 --> 55:20.000
<i>Two days after
the attack began,</i>

55:20.067 --> 55:23.934
<i>the army fired
a high explosive shell
into Nakumatt.</i>

55:28.500 --> 55:31.367
<i>All four terrorists
died in the fire.</i>

55:32.701 --> 55:35.200
<i>Their weapons and what
remained of their bodies</i>

55:35.267 --> 55:38.167
<i>were later recovered
from the ashes.</i>

55:46.968 --> 55:49.000
<i>As Nakumatt burned
to the ground,</i>

55:49.067 --> 55:52.367
<i>the security cameras
stopped recording.</i>

55:54.968 --> 55:57.467
<i>The mall, which was
under army control,</i>

55:57.534 --> 55:59.534
<i>was looted.</i>

56:09.834 --> 56:12.434
<i>The Kenyan government
stood by the actions</i>

56:12.500 --> 56:14.567
<i>of its security forces.</i>

56:14.634 --> 56:17.868
President Uhuru Kenyatta:
<i>I am satisfied that our</i>
<i>disciplined forces</i>

56:17.934 --> 56:20.434
<i>have responded
in a professional</i>

56:20.500 --> 56:22.767
<i>and effective manner.</i>

56:23.834 --> 56:25.234
We have ashamed
and defeated

56:25.300 --> 56:26.834
our
attackers.

56:26.901 --> 56:28.734
Let us
continue
to wage

56:28.801 --> 56:30.367
a relentless
moral war

56:30.434 --> 56:33.767
as our forces conduct
the physical battle.

56:33.834 --> 56:36.767
We shall... triumph.

56:36.834 --> 56:40.000
Narrator:
<i>Hundreds of miles</i>
<i>north in Somalia,</i>

56:40.067 --> 56:43.000
<i>al-Shabaab
also declared a victory.</i>

56:44.234 --> 56:46.467
<i>( man speaking
foreign language )</i>

57:03.901 --> 57:06.100
( singing in
foreign language )

57:09.467 --> 57:11.601
( men singing )

57:14.634 --> 57:16.133
Nura:
<i>Leave alone Islam.</i>

57:16.200 --> 57:18.467
<i>Islam--
the term "Islam,"
it means "peace."</i>

57:18.534 --> 57:20.534
Where is peace?
Where is Islam now?

57:20.601 --> 57:22.133
The term Islam--
where is it

57:22.200 --> 57:23.834
when you kill
innocent children?

57:23.901 --> 57:25.267
When you kill women?

57:25.334 --> 57:27.100
I'm a Muslim myself.

57:28.567 --> 57:31.567
<i>For now,
Westgate remains closed.</i>

57:31.634 --> 57:34.734
<i>It isn't known
when it might open again.</i>

57:35.667 --> 57:37.100
<i>Whatever the intended meaning</i>

57:37.167 --> 57:39.234
<i>of al-Shabaab's
spectacle at Westgate,</i>

57:39.300 --> 57:42.400
<i>the security cameras
revealed it as little more</i>

57:42.467 --> 57:45.901
<i>than the mass murder
of defenseless civilians.</i>

57:47.334 --> 57:49.567
♪ ♪

57:51.033 --> 57:53.434
Amber:
<i>I don't really blame them</i>
<i>as individuals.</i>

57:53.500 --> 57:55.334
<i>They really were
just ordinary men</i>

57:55.400 --> 57:59.500
<i>with very very wrong ideas
about life.</i>

57:59.567 --> 58:01.601
When I spoke to them,
there was a real calm

58:01.667 --> 58:04.200
and determination
about what they were doing.

58:04.267 --> 58:06.100
They were there
to send out a message
to the world--

58:06.167 --> 58:08.767
however messed up
that message was--

58:08.834 --> 58:11.400
and to die doing it.

58:15.334 --> 58:19.100
As long as I've got
breath left inside me...

58:20.100 --> 58:22.167
and a finger...

58:23.234 --> 58:24.868
to squeeze
the trigger...

58:27.834 --> 58:29.834
I won't let...

58:29.901 --> 58:32.801
the same thing
which happened at Westgate...

58:34.400 --> 58:35.934
happen again.

58:36.000 --> 58:38.133
( ominous music playing )
